{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"904cfb24-0357-48ac-a78b-cf8aaad1d45d","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project file:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"902020b9-e1f1-4679-b6f5-3961015bf9a4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":198,"requestId":"5C5D:2CDF90:200929:27BA8E:69F5510D"},"id":"f8b2a13f-65c3-4ef8-b226-4fe4c67e1b42","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:19:15.507Z","parentId":"6b2fe8fe-ded8-46fb-8d3d-1be1e54b869d"}
